Sequence Information.Family: Belongs to the frog skin active peptide family (Brevinin subfamily)
Sequence Information.Target Organism: [Ref.16413829]Gram-negative bacteria:Escherichia coli ATCC 25922 (MIC=3 µM), Klebsiella pneumoniae KK3 9904 (MIC=6 µM), Enterobacter cloacae HNTCC 53001 (MIC=6 µM), Pseudomonas aeruginosa ATCC 27853 (MIC=6 µM), Proteus mirabilis ATCC 25933 (MIC>100 µM);Gram-positive bacteria:Staphylococcus aureus NCTC 8325 (MIC=12.5 µM), Methicillin-resistant Staphylococcus aureus T7/20 (MIC=25 µM), Staphylococcus epidermidis RP62A (MIC=12.5 µM), Enterococcus faecalis ATCC 29212 (MIC=25 µM);Yeast:Candida albicans ATCC 90028 (MIC=100 µM).
Sequence Information.Cytotoxicity: No cytotoxicity information found in the reference(s) presented
Sequence Information.Function: Activity against a range of Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria, but relatively low hemolytic activity against human erythrocytes.

Literature.Title: Antimicrobial peptides from the skin of the Tsushima brown frog Rana tsushimensis.
Literature.Reference: Comp Biochem Physiol C Toxicol Pharmacol. 2006 May;143(1)42-49.
Literature.Author: Conlon JM, Al-Ghaferi N, Abraham B, Sonnevend A, Coquet L, Leprince J, Jouenne T, Vaudry H, Iwamuro S.
